              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} has no significant chronic medical conditions and has never been hospitalised. She has had two prior episodes of upper respiratory tract infection in the past 18 months, both managed conservatively at home. She is up to date with the Czech national vaccination schedule. Her mother reports that {patientName} had a mild febrile illness with a sore throat approximately six months ago that resolved without antibiotic treatment. Tonsillitis is most common in children over age two, and almost every child experiences at least one episode [MEDLINEPLUS:J03.9]. {patientName} attends kindergarten, a well-known risk environment for respiratory infections due to close contact with other children [MEDLINEPLUS:J03.9]. She has no known drug allergies. Her diet is balanced and she takes no regular medications."
          }
        ]
      }
